#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:85
msgid "Overlay Support for PXA27x and later LCD controllers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:87
msgid ""
"PXA27x and later processors support overlay1 and overlay2 on-top of the base "
"framebuffer (although under-neath the base is also possible). They support "
"palette and no-palette RGB formats, as well as YUV formats (only available "
"on overlay2). These overlays have dedicated DMA channels and behave in a "
"similar way as a framebuffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:93
msgid ""
"However, there are some differences between these overlay framebuffers and "
"normal framebuffers, as listed below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:96
msgid ""
"overlay can start at a 32-bit word aligned position within the base "
"framebuffer, which means they have a start (x, y). This information is "
"encoded into var->nonstd (no, var->xoffset and var->yoffset are not for such "
"purpose)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:101
msgid ""
"overlay framebuffer is allocated dynamically according to specified 'struct "
"fb_var_screeninfo', the amount is decided by::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:106
msgid "bpp = 16 -- for RGB565 or RGBT555"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:108
msgid "bpp = 24 -- for YUV444 packed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:110
msgid "bpp = 24 -- for YUV444 planar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:112
msgid "bpp = 16 -- for YUV422 planar (1 pixel = 1 Y + 1/2 Cb + 1/2 Cr)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:114
msgid "bpp = 12 -- for YUV420 planar (1 pixel = 1 Y + 1/4 Cb + 1/4 Cr)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:116
msgid "NOTE:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:118
msgid ""
"overlay does not support panning in x-direction, thus var->xres_virtual will "
"always be equal to var->xres"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:121
msgid ""
"line length of overlay(s) must be on a 32-bit word boundary, for YUV planar "
"modes, it is a requirement for the component with minimum bits per pixel,  e."
"g. for YUV420, Cr component for one pixel is actually 2-bits, it means the "
"line length should be a multiple of 16-pixels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:127
msgid ""
"starting horizontal position (XPOS) should start on a 32-bit word boundary, "
"otherwise the fb_check_var() will just fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../fb/pxafb.rst:130
msgid ""
"the rectangle of the overlay should be within the base plane, otherwise fail"
msgstr ""

